```text
Build a complete responsive frontend-only web app called “HealDrive” (medical transport scheduling) in ONE generation.

Tech stack (must follow):
- Next.js 14+ App Router
- TypeScript (strict, no any)
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui components
- lucide-react icons

Scope:
Frontend ONLY for now. No real backend. Use a clean mocked API layer with an in-memory store and seed data. The UI must look professional, minimal, and accessible. Provide FULL CODE for ALL created/modified files.

Core concept:
Patients (or family helpers “Aidants”) create medical appointments (RDV), then request a medical transport (Taxi/VSL/Ambulance/PMR). The app does smart matching (assign the best available driver), provides live trip tracking (ETA + status timeline), chat, and anti-late alerts with reassignment simulation. Payment is shown only at the end (UI only, optional).

Roles:
- PATIENT
- AIDANT (family helper can manage multiple patients)
- CHAUFFEUR (driver)
- ADMIN

Auth (mock):
- /login with email + password
- On login, store {user, role} in localStorage
- Redirect after login:
  PATIENT/AIDANT -> /patient
  CHAUFFEUR -> /driver
  ADMIN -> /admin
- Protected routes: redirect to /login if not authenticated
- Navbar includes Logout
- Add a “Role switcher” dropdown for demo (allowed even if it changes localStorage)

Routing (App Router pages):
1) /login
2) /patient
3) /patient/rdv/new
4) /patient/trip/[id]
5) /driver
6) /admin

Global layout:
- Top navbar (logo HealDrive, role badge, role switcher, logout)
- Desktop: left sidebar navigation (Patient/Driver/Admin)
- Mobile: bottom navigation
- Use shadcn/ui: Button, Card, Badge, Dialog, DropdownMenu, Tabs, Table, Alert, Toast (Sonner), Sheet/Drawer, Input, Select, Checkbox, Textarea

Data model (types in lib/types.ts):
- UserRole = 'PATIENT' | 'AIDANT' | 'CHAUFFEUR' | 'ADMIN'
- TransportType = 'TAXI' | 'VSL' | 'AMBULANCE' | 'PMR'
- TripStatus = 'DEMANDE' | 'ASSIGNE' | 'ACCEPTE' | 'EN_ROUTE' | 'ARRIVE' | 'TERMINE' | 'ANNULE' | 'REASSIGN'

Entities:
- Patient { id, fullName }
- User { id, fullName, email, role }
- Driver { id, fullName, transportType, available, capabilities: { wheelchair, stretcher, accompaniment }, distanceKmMock, etaMinMock }
- Appointment (RDV) { id, patientId, dateTimeISO, address, durationMin?, notes? }
- Trip { id, appointmentId, patientId, pickupAddress, dropoffAddress, requiredTransportType, needs: {wheelchair, stretcher, accompaniment}, status, etaMinutes, distanceKm, assignedDriverId?, riskLate? }
- Message { id, tripId, senderRole, senderName, content, createdAtISO }

Mock API (lib/api.ts):
- In-memory store + realistic seed data:
  * 1 admin, 1 aidant, 2 patients, 3 drivers (Taxi, VSL, Ambulance/PMR capable)
  * 2 appointments
  * 1 trip DEMANDE
- Functions returning Promises with small setTimeout latency:
  * authLogin(email,password) -> user
  * getCurrentUser() from localStorage
  * listPatients(), listAppointments(patientId), createAppointment()
  * createTrip(request) -> trip (auto smart match assigns driver and sets status ASSIGNE)
  * getTrip(id), listTripsByPatient(patientId)
  * driverSetAvailability(driverId, available)
  * listNearbyRequestsForDriver(driverId) (DEMANDE/ASSIGNE)
  * driverAcceptTrip(tripId, driverId) -> status ACCEPTE
  * updateTripStatus(tripId, status)
  * simulateDriverDelay(tripId, plusMinutes=10) (increase ETA)
  * simulateDriverCancel(tripId) -> sets ANNULE then reassigns to REASSIGN/ASSIGNE with another compatible driver if available
  * listMessages(tripId), sendMessage(tripId, senderRole, senderName, content)

Smart matching (mocked but “credible”):
- Choose driver that is:
  * available = true
  * transportType matches requiredTransportType OR has capability for PMR if required is PMR
  * satisfies needs: wheelchair/stretcher/accompaniment
- From compatible drivers, pick the one with smallest distanceKmMock
- Set trip.distanceKm + etaMinutes from driver mock values
- Set assignedDriverId

Anti-late logic (UI + API):
- For a trip linked to an appointment:
  riskLate = (now + etaMinutes + 10min) > appointment.dateTime
- Show an Alert if riskLate is true with:
  * “Risk of being late”
  * suggested actions: “Contact driver” and “Request reassignment”
- In /patient/trip/[id] add buttons:
  * “Simulate driver delay (+10 min)”
  * “Simulate driver cancel”
  These update riskLate and status accordingly.

Patient/Aidant dashboard (/patient):
- If role PATIENT:
  * show appointment list (cards) with date/time, address, notes, duration
  * CTA: “Create appointment”
  * On each appointment card: “Request transport” (opens Dialog)
- If role AIDANT:
  * show a patient selector dropdown (e.g., Mom/Dad)
  * appointments and trips filtered by selected patient
- “Request transport” Dialog:
  * select appointment (default the one clicked)
  * pickup address input (default “Home”)
  * transport type select (TAXI/VSL/AMBULANCE/PMR)
  * needs checkboxes (wheelchair, stretcher, accompaniment)
  * submit -> createTrip -> toast success -> navigate to /patient/trip/[id]

Appointment creation page (/patient/rdv/new):
- Form with date+time picker (can be text input ISO for simplicity), address, duration, notes
- Submit -> createAppointment -> toast -> go back to /patient

Trip tracking page (/patient/trip/[id]):
- Header: Trip ID + status Badge + RDV time
- “Live tracking” section:
  * Map placeholder card (no real map)
  * Driver info card (name, type, availability)
  * ETA big number
- Timeline component for statuses:
  DEMANDE -> ASSIGNE -> ACCEPTE -> EN_ROUTE -> ARRIVE -> TERMINE
- Simulation:
  * Every 5 seconds decrease ETA (until 0) and auto-advance status (ASSIGNE->ACCEPTE->EN_ROUTE->ARRIVE->TERMINE)
  * Keep it deterministic and stoppable if ANNULE
- Chat:
  * Messages panel (desktop right column, mobile in Sheet/Drawer)
  * Input + Send
  * Quick message buttons:
    “I’m late”, “Appointment running late”, “I’m at the entrance”
- If status TERMINE:
  * show “Close & Pay” card (UI only):
    - price estimate (simple: base + km*rate mock)
    - buttons “Bon de transport” / “Card (simulated)”
    - on click: toast “Payment recorded (mock)”

Driver dashboard (/driver):
- Availability toggle
- “Nearby requests” list showing pickup, destination, required type, needs badges, distance, ETA
- Accept button -> driverAcceptTrip -> show “Current trip” panel with:
  * status update buttons: EN_ROUTE, ARRIVE, TERMINE
  * open chat with patient (reuse chat component)
- Toasts for actions

Admin dashboard (/admin):
- Table of all trips with columns:
  createdAt (or derived), patient, driver, type, status, riskLate badge
- Filters: status dropdown + search input
- Row click opens Drawer with trip details + messages preview

UX requirements:
- Clean spacing, consistent typography, responsive layout
- Use loading states for mock API calls
- Use Error boundaries or simple error UI
- No external map APIs
- Don’t require server-side rendering data; everything client-side is fine for MVP
- Provide clear file structure (app routes, components, lib)

Deliverable:
Return the full Next.js project code (all key files) as text, including:
- app layout + pages
- components (Navbar, Sidebar, Timeline, Chat, Cards, Dialogs)
- lib/types.ts, lib/api.ts, lib/auth.ts (if needed)
- Tailwind + shadcn/ui setup references
Make sure it runs after installing dependencies and running `npm run dev`.
```
